## 3️⃣ DIGITAL ANCHOR MIGRATION (optional but satisfying)

If you like the idea of the *digital* anchor moving with you, make it **draggable** and then **lock** it in place once you’ve found a comfortable spot.

### A. Add a tiny draggable script (≈ 30 sec)

Paste this at the **bottom** of `app.js` (after the existing anchor code).

```js
// ---- Draggable digital anchor (once) ----
const anchor = document.querySelector('#anchorDot') || document.createElement('div');
anchor.id = 'anchorDot';
anchor.style.position = 'fixed';
anchor.style.right = '8px';
anchor.style.bottom = '8px';
anchor.style.width = '6px';
anchor.style.height = '6px';
anchor.style.background = '#cce6ff';
anchor.style.borderRadius = '50%';
anchor.title = 'Drag to lock your anchor';
document.body.appendChild(anchor);

// Simple drag logic
let dragging = false;
anchor.addEventListener('mousedown', e => { dragging = true; e.preventDefault(); });
window.addEventListener('mousemove', e => {
  if (!dragging) return;
  anchor.style.right = `${window.innerWidth - e.clientX - 3}px`;
  anchor.style.bottom = `${window.innerHeight - e.clientY - 3}px`;
});
window.addEventListener('mouseup', () => dragging = false);
```

### B. How to use it

1. **Refresh** the page.  
2. **Hover** the tiny dot – the cursor will become a pointer.  
3. **Click‑drag** it to any corner (or to the middle of the screen if you prefer).  
4. **Release** – it stays where you dropped it.  

Now the dot is **your personal anchor** that you can move whenever the visual rhythm feels “off”. It no longer feels like it’s pulling the sticky; it’s simply a visual reminder you control.

