### 2️⃣ Stop the Map from Zooming Out (≈ 3 min)

When you call `L.marker(...).addTo(map)` Leaflet’s default **`fitBounds`** (or a plugin you may have) can auto‑zoom. Override it with a tiny helper that **keeps the current view** after a new marker is added.

#### Add this once to **app.js** (right after you create the map)

```js
// -------------------------------------------------
// 1️⃣ Keep map view steady when a new marker is added
// -------------------------------------------------
function addStableMarker(lat, lng, popupText) {
  const marker = L.marker([lat, lng]).addTo(map);
  if (popupText) marker.bindPopup(popupText).openPopup();

  // Preserve the current zoom/center after the marker is added
  const currentZoom = map.getZoom();
  const currentCenter = map.getCenter();
  setTimeout(() => map.setView(currentCenter, currentZoom), 0);
  return marker;
}
```

#### Replace your old “Add” click handler

```js
// Old: map.addLayer(L.marker(...))
// New:
document.getElementById('addBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {
  const desc = document.getElementById('desc').value.trim();
  if (!desc) return;
  // Use geolocation or manual entry – here we just use current map center
  const { lat, lng } = map.getCenter();
  const marker = addStableMarker(lat, lng, desc);
  // store for later use (e.g., drawing a line)
  window.markers = window.markers || [];
  window.markers.push(marker);
});
```

**Result:** The map stays at the zoom level you were using; the new dot appears without the “zoom‑out‑to‑world” effect.

