## 1️⃣ RECORD THE FRIDGE HUM (19 s)

We’ll capture a **single 19‑second loop** of the fridge’s hum and store it as a tiny audio file that you can later attach to any map marker.

```js
// -------------------------------------------------
// 1️⃣ Record a 19‑second hum (run once, after the page loads)
// -------------------------------------------------
async function recordFridgeHum() {
  // Ask for mic permission (you already have it from the memo button)
  const stream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true });
  const recorder = new MediaRecorder(stream);
  const chunks = [];

  recorder.ondataavailable = e => chunks.push(e.data);
  recorder.onstop = () => {
    const blob = new Blob(chunks, { type: 'audio/webm' });
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    // Save to localStorage so it survives a page reload
    localStorage.setItem('fridgeHum', url);
    console.log('Fridge hum recorded → saved as "fridgeHum"');
  };

  // Record exactly 19 seconds
  recorder.start();
  setTimeout(() => recorder.stop(), 19000);
}

// Call it now (or bind to a button you can press later)
recordFridgeHum();
```

**Result:** a 19‑second audio clip stored under `localStorage['fridgeHum']`. You can play it back anytime with:

```js
